Gauteng premier David Makhura says there's a decline in the number of active COVID-19 cases in the province. Gauteng has 24 new cases, while 15 people have died and 1,015 patients have recovered. #Day42ofLockdown JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng premier David Makhura says there's a decline in the number of active COVID-19 cases in the province. Gauteng has 24 new cases, while 15 people have died and 1,015 patients have recovered. WATCH: Gauteng Command Council gives update on COVID-19 Makhura said people with underlying medical conditions like high blood pressure, heart problems and chronic respiratory illnesses develop complications if they contract COVID-19. According to the provincial report, Gauteng doctors emphasise early interventions are important including oxygenation, fluid supportive treatment, prone position, and blood-thinning to reducing complications and mortality. READ: COVID-19: Gauteng Health Dept screen over 1.2m He has outlined Gauteng's plans to deal with the virus. The premier strongly urged people to continue practicing social distancing. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.